==Arabic==

===Verb I===
'''{{ARchar|رجل}}''' (rájila)

# to go on foot, to [[walk]].

===Verb II===
'''{{ARchar|رجّل}}''' (rájjala)

# to [[comb]] (the hair).
# to let down (the hair).

===Verb V===
'''{{ARchar|[[ترجل]]}}''' (tarájjala)

# to go on foot, to [[walk]].
# to [[dismount]].
# to behave like a man, to assume masculine mannerisms.

===Verb VIII===
'''{{ARchar|[[ارتجل]]}}''' (irtájala)

# to [[improvise]], to [[extemporize]].

===Verb X===
'''{{ARchar|[[استرجل]]}}''' (istárjala)

# to become a man, to reach manhood.
# to [[grow]] up.
# to act like a man.
# to display masculine mannerisms.

===Transliteration===
*ISO 233: raǧul
*UNGEGN: rajul

====Noun====
'''{{ARchar|رجل}}''' (rájul) {{m}}, {{ARchar|[[رجال]]}} (rijāl) {{p}}

#[[man]]

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|رجل}}''' (rijl) {{f}}, {{ARchar|[[ارجل]]}} (’árjul) {{p}}

# [[leg]], [[foot]]

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|رجل}}''' (rijl) {{m}}, {{ARchar|[[ارجال]]}} (’arjāl) {{p}}

# [[swarm]] (especially, of locusts)
# [[purslane]] (''Portulaca oleracea L.'')

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|رجل}}''' (rijl) {{m}}

# going on foot, [[pedestrian]], [[walking]]

